---
<section id="vision" class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-32 border-y border-white/5">
  <div class="dashboard-card p-12 md:p-16 border-none bg-transparent">
    <div class="corner-marker marker-tl w-8 h-8 opacity-40"></div>
    <div class="corner-marker marker-br w-8 h-8 opacity-40"></div>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr,2fr] gap-16">
      
      <!-- Left side: The Mission -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-black text-accent tracking-[0.3em] uppercase opacity-90">STRATEGIC_THESIS // REV_04</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black font-outfit text-white uppercase tracking-tighter leading-[0.9]">
          War on<br/>
          <span class="text-accent">Middleware.</span>
        </h2>
        
        <div class="mt-8 p-6 border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 text-[10px] font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-widest leading-relaxed">
          <span class="text-accent-muted mr-2">[GOAL]</span> SYSTEM_SELF_CUSTODY<br/>
          <span class="text-accent-muted mr-2">[TARGET]</span> RENT_SEEKING_MIDDLEWARE<br/>
          <span class="text-accent-muted mr-2">[MODE]</span> DIRECT_NETWORK_EXECUTION
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right side: The Text -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-mute leading-relaxed text-lg font-medium">
          <p>
            The next era of software is owned, not rented. Blockchains and hashgraphs handle settlement
            and consensus. <span class="text-white">Edge compute handles execution.</span> The user holds the keys. 
            The middle layer — custodial exchanges, subscription apps, third-party RPCs, opaque algorithms — collapses.
          </p>
          <p>
            I build software that talks directly to the networks. No intermediaries. No vendor lock.
            No rent extracted on top of code anyone could write.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="h-px bg-white/5"></div>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 text-mute leading-relaxed text-lg font-medium">
          <p>
            The long arc is a single, self-custodied connective layer across the systems and chains
            worth owning — Hedera and Hyperliquid first, then the rest. 
          </p>
          <p>
            Companies make money by providing genuine ongoing services and information edge — not by 
            rent-seeking on middleware. That's the new economic opportunity, and it's a big one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
